Interface ConcernRetractionObserver

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface ConcernRetractionObserver
extends java.io.Serializable
    This interface is implemented by MainViewModel and used by ConcernDetailViewModel to update a given concerns statuses when it has been retracted.
    Invariants:
    none.
    History Properties:
    none.

    • Method Detail

      • concernRetracted

        void concernRetracted(@NonNull
                      android.content.Context context,
                      @NonNull
                      ConcernWrapper concern)
        Used only by ConcernDetailViewModel. Informs the MainViewModel that a concern has been retracted so the concern can be updated.
        Parameters:
        context - The context of the ConcernDetailActivity
        concern - The concern which was retracted
        preconditions:
        - context and concern are not null - index is in the range: [ 0, MainViewModel.concernList.size()-1 ]
        modifies:
        - The concern at index 'index' is replaced with 'concern' (The index and concern in single quotes refers to the parameters of this method).
